dee 🌼 doris 24-Jun-21 07:34 PM
THE CLOCK TICKS ⏰ It’s a bright Thursday afternoon when a young man calls the agency asking for help with what he believes to be an anomalous disappearance. His younger sister had gone outside to check on a wild bunny hopping around in the backyard, when he went to call her back inside after ten minutes, she and the bunny were gone and the backyard had changed. He tried calling other agencies but since she only just disappeared they said he would have to wait at least 24 hours to file a proper missing case. He has asked you to meet him at his house ASAP. It doesn't seem like the kind of case that requires more than 6 people but hey a case is a case. The clients home is located in one of the lusher areas of the city just outside the downtown core, a neighborhood where each house has trimmed hedges and gardens. A young man with dark hair dyed blue greets you by the door, thick brows furrowed from worry, but relieved to see you all.
